cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically monocular depth estimation, and proposes a semi-supervised approach using deep neural networks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of supervised training and data ensemble strategies, which are common in machine learning and deep learning, suggesting that cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions road detection, which falls under the sub-category cs.RO (Robotics), and the use of feature representations, which is relevant to cs.MM (Multimedia).
